Data Visualization from ETL Process
Theory (Write in Exam)
Introduction

Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) is the process of:

Extracting data from different sources
Transforming data into a proper format
Loading data into a target system

After ETL processing, Data Visualization is used to represent data graphically for better analysis and decision making.

Visualization helps users understand:

Trends
Patterns
Comparisons
Business insights
ETL Process with Visualization
Data Sources
(Excel, SQL Server, Oracle)
            ↓
         Extract
            ↓
       Transform
(Clean, Filter, Format)
            ↓
           Load
     (Target Database)
            ↓
     Data Visualization
 (Charts, Graphs, Dashboards)
Types of Data Visualization
Visualization	Purpose
Bar Chart	Compare values
Line Chart	Show trends over time
Pie Chart	Show percentage distribution
Histogram	Show data frequency
Scatter Plot	Show relationship between variables
Advantages
Easy understanding of large data
Better business decisions
Detect trends and anomalies
Improves reporting efficiency
Python Program for ETL and Data Visualization
Required Libraries
pip install pandas matplotlib openpyxl sqlalchemy
Python Code
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sqlalchemy import create_engine

# -----------------------------------
# EXTRACT
# Read data from Excel
# -----------------------------------

data = pd.read_excel("sales_data.xlsx")

print("Extracted Data:")
print(data)

# -----------------------------------
# TRANSFORM
# Clean and process data
# -----------------------------------

# Remove null values
data = data.dropna()

# Convert column names to uppercase
data.columns = data.columns.str.upper()

print("\nTransformed Data:")
print(data)

# -----------------------------------
# LOAD
# Store data into target database
# -----------------------------------

engine = create_engine(
    "sqlite:///sales_database.db"
)

data.to_sql(
    "sales",
    engine,
    if_exists='replace',
    index=False
)

print("\nData loaded successfully.")

# -----------------------------------
# DATA VISUALIZATION
# -----------------------------------

# Example: Sales by Product

product_sales = data.groupby('PRODUCT')['SALES'].sum()

plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))

product_sales.plot(kind='bar')

plt.title("Sales by Product")
plt.xlabel("Product")
plt.ylabel("Total Sales")

plt.show()
Explanation of Program
Step	Description
Extract	Reads data from Excel file
Transform	Cleans and formats data
Load	Stores data into database
Visualization	Creates bar chart for analysis
